{"id":1220833782,"question_id":15,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2Â weeks","timestamp":1712037823,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"879 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1220833782/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"3Sum","memory":"52 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {\n        int target = 0;\n        Arrays.sort(nums);\n        Set<List<Integer>> s = new HashSet<>();\n        List<List<Integer>> output = new ArrayList<>();\n        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++){\n            int j = i + 1;\n            int k = nums.length - 1;\n            while (j < k) {\n                int sum = nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k];\n                if (sum == target) {\n                    s.add(Arrays.asList(nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]));\n                    j++;\n                    k--;\n                } else if (sum < target) {\n                    j++;\n                } else {\n                    k--;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        output.addAll(s);\n        return output;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"3sum","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
